Political activist, Deji Adeyanju has alleged that President Muhammadu Buhari-led administration is planning to increase the price of fuel to N450 per litre. He raised the alarm over moves to increase the pump price of fuel in Nigeria on Saturday in a tweet. Also Read: Zainab Ahmed: FG Will Pay Nigerians Transport Allowance After Fuel Subsidy Removal Adeyanju’s claim comes a day after the nation’s Finance Minister, Zainab Ahmed said fuel subsidy is costing Nigeria resources that should have been used for education and health. He wrote: “They are planning to increase fuel price to N450 per litre. The clowns that promised CHANGE in 2015 are determined to kill Nigerians with suffering and hunger.”